{"key":"processedPost-5641051","value":{"id":5641051,"first":5640554,"last":5649231,"when":1147873043,"utime":"05/17/06 04:37 PM","content":"No you can't use an oven to sterilize.  Water can not exist in a liquid state above 212F/100C. If you heated the interior of your jars to 250F, the grains would be drier than they were at the store when you bought them.<br /><br />Air is a terrible conductor of heat.  Water will transfer heat into a substrate for pasteurizing much faster than air will.  <br />RR","title":"Re: sterilizing in a roaster oven?"}}